OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1772705110
OL,3,CRoyal Marines line street to pay
OL,4,Ctribute to Second World War veteran
OL,6,FMr Wren, who was held by the Japanese
OL,7,Fduring the war in the Far East, was
OL,8,Frejected by both the RAF and the
OL,9,FBritish Army at the age of 19.
OL,11,FBut, encouraged by his uncle, he later
OL,12,Fjoined the Royal Marines.
OL,14,FAfter completing his training, he was
OL,15,Fassigned to a First World War-era
OL,16,Fbattle-cruiser, HMS Repulse, which was
OL,17,Finvolved in the hunt for the Bismarck.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1772705110
OL,3,CRoyal Marines line street to pay
OL,4,Ctribute to Second World War veteran
OL,6,FDeployed to the Far East in a bid to
OL,7,Fdeter Japanese aggression in the
OL,8,FPacific, Repulse lasted just 80
OL,9,Fminutes in battle before Mr Wren and
OL,10,Fhis shipmates were caught by enemy
OL,11,Fbombers in the South China Sea on
OL,12,FDecember 10, 1941.
OL,14,FPreviously speaking to comrades in the
OL,15,FRoyal Marines Association, he recalled
OL,16,Fthe moment the alarm sounded on the
OL,17,Fship.
OL,19,FMr Wren, who was originally from
OL,20,FSussex, said: "I dropped my tea and
OL,21,Fheaded to my action station.
OL,26,@|D@OOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
