OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1772705110
OL,3,CRoyal Marines line street to pay
OL,4,Ctribute to Second World War veteran
OL,6,F"The noise was terrific, it was one
OL,7,Fbig noisy battle. There was no panic
OL,8,Fthough, we'd been through the routines
OL,9,Fso regularly that we just got on it.
OL,10,FEveryone knew their role and we had
OL,11,Fsuch a good crew. We all had faith in
OL,12,Feach other."
OL,14,FTwo months later, he was captured by
OL,15,Fthe Japanese as he attempted to escape
OL,16,Ffrom Singapore. He spent the remainder
OL,17,Fof the conflict in prisoner-of-war
OL,18,Fcamps where he endured harsh treatment
OL,19,Funtil the news of Japan's surrender in
OL,20,FAugust 1945.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@LO]
